# Content SEO quality (kit law)

Same bar for every subject and stack. Subject changes topics only.

- Research: ≥2000 words, 20+ sources, domain study not SERP report
- Articles: TL;DR, FAQ 5–6, YAML seo block, no guillemets `«»`, inline links in ≥4 H2s
- Links: exactly 1 homepage link, denylist clean, Phase 6 audit before publish
- Publish: `node scripts/publish-draft-to-content.mjs [NNNN]` — no raw copy / batch bypass
- Titles: draft `seo.title` = topic only; live `metaTitle` carries brand suffix (not H1)
- Validators: `node .content-kit/validators/check-research.mjs` and `check-article.mjs`

Standards: `.content-kit/standards/`. Profile: `content-pipeline.profile.json`.
